      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH). Both are directly used in the regulatory acceptance criterion. Shear stress exposure time integral is secondary QoI informing worst-case operating point identification. All QoIs are directly traceable to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
