      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selection justified with reference to literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on documented superiority for adverse pressure gradient flows in centrifugal pump passages (Menter 1994; FDA benchmark literature). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model used; sensitivity to exponent coefficients assessed with ±10% perturbation yielding < 8% change in NIH. Model form uncertainty quantified and within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs identified, uncertainty ranges documented, and sensitivity analysis performed for dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (0.0035 ± 0.0003 Pa·s), inlet flow rate (±2%), and impeller speed (±10 RPM) identified as dominant inputs via one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis. NIH sensitivity to viscosity: 4.2% per 10% viscosity change. All input uncertainties within measurement capability. Material property sources documented from ASTM and published literature."
    },
